<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p>I&#39;ve got USB microphone Superlux E205U MK II and it works fine on windows, however on Linux it keeps getting detected as &#39;Bravo-X USB Audio&#39;.</p> <p>Randomly(rarely) it gets detected properly:</p> <pre><code>[44035.022916] usb 1-8: new full-speed USB device number 24 using xhci_hcd [44035.433652] usb 1-8: language id specifier not provided by device, defaulting to English [44035.655669] usb 1-8: New USB device found, idVendor=262a, idProduct=1770, bcdDevice= 0.01 [44035.655675] usb 1-8: New USB device strings: Mfr=1, Product=2, SerialNumber=0 [44035.655676] usb 1-8: Product: Superlux E205U MKII [44035.689624] hid-generic 0003:262A:1770.0023: hidraw10: USB HID v1.00 Device [Superlux E205U MKII] on usb-0000:03:00.0-8/input0 </code></pre> <p>However most of the time:</p> <pre><code>[44887.988352] usb 1-8: New USB device found, idVendor=262a, idProduct=9023, bcdDevice= 0.01 [44887.988356] usb 1-8: New USB device strings: Mfr=1, Product=2, SerialNumber=0 [44887.988358] usb 1-8: Product: Bravo-X USB Audio [44887.988359] usb 1-8: Manufacturer: SAVITECH [44888.006503] input: SAVITECH Bravo-X USB Audio as /devices/pci0000:00/0000:00:01.3/0000:03:00.0/usb1/1-8/1-8:1.0/0003:262A:9023.0024/input/input50 [44888.061448] hid-generic 0003:262A:9023.0024: input,hidraw10: USB HID v1.00 Device [SAVITECH Bravo-X USB Audio] on usb-0000:03:00.0-8/input0 </code></pre> <p>Things I&#39;ve tried:</p> <p>- Writing a script that unbinds and binds usb til it detects proper microphone in lsusb</p> <p>- Removing all other usb devices and plugging in microphone alone</p> <p>- Every other port</p> <p>- Added usbcore.autosuspend=-1 to kernel flags</p> <p>- Installed missing firmware, noticeably upd72020x-fw which seemed to be related to USB chipset</p> <p>&#x200B;</p> <p>My mobo: B450 Tomahawk MAX</p> <p>Edit: Tried with xhci_hcd instead of drivers/usb/bind and now I can get it to detect properly, but it says it doesn&#39;t have enough bandwith for new device state (despite being only thing plugged in). Script I&#39;ve used:</p> <pre><code>#!/bin/bash cd /sys/bus/pci/drivers/xhci_hcd/ echo &quot;Trying to fix&quot; for file in ????:??:??.? ; do echo -n &quot;$file&quot; &gt; unbind echo -n &quot;$file&quot; &gt; bind done while lsusb | grep &#39;Bravo-X\|SA9023&#39;; do echo &quot;Retrying fix&quot; for file in ????:??:??.? ; do echo -n &quot;$file&quot; &gt; unbind echo -n &quot;$file&quot; &gt; bind done done echo &quot;Done&quot; </code></pre> <p>Edit 2: Might be worth mentioning, sometimes windows also displays &quot;not enough resources&quot; notification, but mic works despite that and it rarely ever happens.</p> <p>&#x200B;</p> <p>Edit 3: For anyone running into this issue, running that script multiple times fixes things, however it&#39;s still inconvenient and I am still trying to find less hacky solution.</p> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/Damianu"> /u/Damianu </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/archlinux/comments/w0kn8a/issue_with_wrong_usbs_productid/">[link]</a></span> &#32; <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/archlinux/comments/w0kn8a/issue_with_wrong_usbs_productid/">[comments]</a></span>